Final patch in the audio-refactor cluster (#31 / 0013-0017). Migrates
Organya's music-synthesis hook from SDL2_mixer's global Mix_HookMusic
callback to SDL3's pull-driven AudioStream pattern bound to a dedicated
MIX_Track via MIX_SetTrackAudioStream.

DESIGN DEVIATION FROM ORIGINAL PLAN — see "Why not MIX_SetTrackRawCallback"
section below. The deviation is technically cleaner and saves CPU on the
cooperative scheduler; documenting prominently because nxengine and I
discussed an earlier design that this supersedes.

Architectural change:
- SDL2_mixer had ONE global music callback (Mix_HookMusic) that the
  mixer called whenever it needed PCM bytes. Pull-driven, single hook.
- SDL3 has no such global hook. The replacement is a per-track input
  source — either a MIX_Audio (finite), an SDL_AudioStream (streaming),
  or callbacks for modifying mid-pipeline. We use an SDL_AudioStream
  with a get-callback that fires when the stream needs more data.

Pipeline:
  Organya._musicCallback (UNCHANGED — S16 stereo synth into Uint8* buffer)
        ↓
  organyaStreamCallback (new SDL_AudioStreamCallback adapter; resizes
        scratch buf, calls _musicCallback, SDL_PutAudioStreamData)
        ↓
  _organya_stream (SDL_AudioStream, S16 stereo SAMPLE_RATE both src+dst)
        ↓
  MIX_SetTrackAudioStream binds it as input to _organya_track
        ↓
  Mixer pulls from track when it needs frames; SDL3 audio device
  pipeline handles S16 → device-format conversion downstream.

Lifecycle:
- start() lazy-creates _organya_stream + _organya_track (kept alive
  across stop/start cycles to avoid allocation churn).
- stop() calls MIX_StopTrack(track, 0); track + stream stay alive.
- shutdown() destroys both via MIX_DestroyTrack + SDL_DestroyAudioStream.
  Order is important: track first (mixer stops pulling from stream),
  stream second.

Why not MIX_SetTrackRawCallback (deviation rationale):
- I (sdl-engine) initially proposed using SDL3_mixer's
  MIX_SetTrackRawCallback for the Organya generator path, with a
  manual S16 → float conversion at the boundary. nxengine reviewed
  and confirmed Organya should stay S16-internal with conversion at
  the boundary. Both correct.
- Closer reading of SDL3_mixer's API docs surfaced that
  MIX_SetTrackRawCallback is for MODIFYING decoded PCM mid-pipeline,
  NOT for SOURCING audio from a generator. The track must already
  have an input source (MIX_Audio or SDL_AudioStream); the raw
  callback fires AFTER decode, BEFORE gain/positioning/etc. To use
  it as a generator we'd need a dummy silent MIX_Audio source bound
  to the track and overwrite its silence — works, but indirect.
- The SDL_AudioStream + get-callback pattern is the documented "I
  generate PCM on demand" primitive in SDL3 core. MIX_SetTrackAudioStream
  is the documented way to feed a track from such a stream. So this
  patch uses that pattern instead.
- Side benefit: skips the manual S16 → float pass nxengine and I were
  designing around. The SDL3 audio device pipeline does the format
  conversion downstream of us, saving a `samples × 2` floating-point
  divide per chunk. nxengine's risk #2 (audio-callback duration on
  cooperative scheduler) is reduced.
- Synthesis correctness invariant (nxengine's review territory) is
  PRESERVED — Organya internal mixer is still S16-only. Only the
  data-handoff path differs from the original sketch.

API mapping:
- Mix_HookMusic(callback, NULL)  → SDL_CreateAudioStream +
                                    SDL_SetAudioStreamGetCallback +
                                    MIX_CreateTrack +
                                    MIX_SetTrackAudioStream +
                                    MIX_PlayTrack
- Mix_HookMusic(NULL, NULL)      → MIX_StopTrack(track, 0)
                                    (track + stream stay alive)

New callback signature (organyaStreamCallback, replaces myMusicPlayer
trampoline at the SDL boundary):
- SDL2_mixer: void (*)(void *udata, uint8_t *stream, int len)
- SDL3 core:  void (*)(void *userdata, SDL_AudioStream *stream,
                       int additional_amount, int total_amount)
The new callback resizes the scratch S16 buffer to additional_amount
bytes (in int16_t units), calls _musicCallback to fill it (signature
unchanged — still writes Uint8* of N bytes), then SDL_PutAudioStreamData.

State:
- New private members on Organya class (in Organya.h):
  - MIX_Track *_organya_track = nullptr;
  - SDL_AudioStream *_organya_stream = nullptr;
  - std::vector<int16_t> _s16_scratch;  (resize-on-demand, never shrinks)
- friend declaration grants organyaStreamCallback access to _s16_scratch.

Synchronous-only invariant (per docs/SDL3-MIGRATION.md § 3): no
SDL_CreateThread, no std::thread, the get-callback fires on SDL3-DOS's
cooperative audio pump. Critical for Organya specifically because the
synth is CPU-dense — no thread to offload to.

Behavioral preservation:
- _musicCallback's S16 synth math is byte-identical to upstream.
- _musicCallback's "if (!song.playing) memset to silence" early-return
  preserved. Pause/resume keep working via the existing flag toggle —
  no MIX_PauseTrack needed.
- pause/resume members unchanged; they toggle song.playing; the
  callback returns silence when paused; the track keeps mixing silence.
- SAMPLE_RATE pinning matches mixer spec from 0017 (44100 stereo S16).
  Phase 9 lever 1 rate-change is a separate atomic concern with its own
  audio-capture gate.

Closes the 0013-0017 audio-refactor series. Together with 0017
(SoundManager foundation), 0013 (Pixtone CVT → AudioStream),
0014 (Pixtone Mix→MIX + 64-track pool), and 0016 (Ogg Mix_Music
→ MIX_Audio + MIX_Track), this patch produces a tree where every
SDL2_mixer / SDL_AudioCVT API call has been replaced. `make nxengine`
should configure + compile end-to-end after this lands.

LISTEN-CHECK at audio-capture gate (per nxengine's risk flag): silence
floor / quantization noise that wasn't there pre-migration. The
deviation to AudioStream means we no longer have a manual S16→float
conversion to surface FP truncation artifacts at — but SDL3 core's
device-side conversion still does S16→whatever-the-device-takes, and
any truncation bug would surface as the same kind of audible artifact.
Capture A/B remains valid: same Organya source bytes pre and post
migration; same SAMPLE_RATE; only the path-to-device differs.
---
 src/sound/Organya.cpp | 121 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 src/sound/Organya.h   |  30 +++++++++++
 2 files changed, 146 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/sound/Organya.cpp b/src/sound/Organya.cpp
index bb931e1..c438f41 100644
--- a/src/sound/Organya.cpp
+++ b/src/sound/Organya.cpp
@@ -14,8 +14,8 @@
 #include "Pixtone.h"
 #include "SoundManager.h"
 
-#include <SDL.h>
-#include <SDL_mixer.h>
+#include <SDL3/SDL.h>
+#include <SDL3_mixer/SDL_mixer.h>
 #include <cmath>
 #include <cstring>
 #include <fstream>
@@ -53,7 +53,24 @@ Organya *Organya::getInstance()
 
 void Organya::init() {}
 
-void Organya::shutdown() {}
+void Organya::shutdown()
+{
+  // DOS-PORT: tear down the SDL3 audio-stream + MIX_Track allocated lazily
+  // by start(). Order: destroy the track first (so the mixer stops pulling
+  // from the stream), then destroy the stream. Run before SoundManager's
+  // MIX_DestroyMixer (Organya::shutdown is invoked from SoundManager::
+  // shutdown ahead of MIX_DestroyMixer, so order is correct).
+  if (_organya_track)
+  {
+    MIX_DestroyTrack(_organya_track);
+    _organya_track = nullptr;
+  }
+  if (_organya_stream)
+  {
+    SDL_DestroyAudioStream(_organya_stream);
+    _organya_stream = nullptr;
+  }
+}
 
 //------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
@@ -324,6 +341,56 @@ bool Organya::load(const std::string &fname)
 
 std::function<void(void *, uint8_t *, int)> musicCallback;
 
+// DOS-PORT: SDL3 audio pipeline adapter for Organya's S16-internal
+// synthesis. SDL2_mixer's Mix_HookMusic was a global void(udata, Uint8*,
+// int) callback that the mixer called when it needed PCM bytes. SDL3's
+// equivalent is an SDL_AudioStreamCallback that we register on the
+// _organya_stream; the mixer (via MIX_SetTrackAudioStream) pulls from
+// the stream as needed, and the stream invokes this callback when it
+// runs short — exact same "produce on demand" semantics as the old hook.
+//
+// We deliberately use SDL3 core's SDL_AudioStream rather than
+// SDL3_mixer's MIX_SetTrackRawCallback here because the latter is for
+// MODIFYING decoded audio mid-pipeline, not for SOURCING audio from a
+// generator. (RawCallback would require attaching a dummy silent
+// MIX_Audio source and overwriting it — an unnecessary indirection.)
+// The AudioStream path also lets the SDL3 audio device pipeline handle
+// the S16 → device-format conversion downstream of us, saving the CPU
+// cost of a manual S16 → float pass in this callback. Important because
+// Organya synthesis is CPU-dense and the callback runs on SDL3-DOS's
+// cooperative scheduler (no thread to offload to).
+//
+// Note this is a deviation from the original boundary-conversion design
+// I (sdl-engine) discussed with nxengine — the deviation arose from
+// reading SDL3_mixer's API docs more carefully and discovering RawCallback
+// isn't a generator primitive. The new path keeps Organya internal S16
+// (nxengine's correctness invariant) and is strictly cheaper at runtime.
+static void SDLCALL organyaStreamCallback(void *userdata, SDL_AudioStream *stream,
+                                          int additional_amount, int /*total_amount*/)
+{
+  if (additional_amount <= 0) return;
+
+  Organya *self = static_cast<Organya *>(userdata);
+  // The old _musicCallback writes S16 stereo PCM into a Uint8* buffer of
+  // a given byte length. We resize our scratch buffer to that byte count
+  // (in int16_t units) and hand it the buffer reinterpreted as Uint8*.
+  size_t needed_int16s = (size_t)additional_amount / sizeof(int16_t);
+  if (self->_s16_scratch.size() < needed_int16s)
+  {
+    self->_s16_scratch.resize(needed_int16s);  // never shrinks
+  }
+  self->_musicCallback(nullptr,
+                       reinterpret_cast<uint8_t *>(self->_s16_scratch.data()),
+                       (uint32_t)additional_amount);
+  if (!SDL_PutAudioStreamData(stream, self->_s16_scratch.data(), additional_amount))
+  {
+    LOG_ERROR("SDL_PutAudioStreamData (Organya): {}", SDL_GetError());
+  }
+}
+
+// Legacy trampoline retained for any external references (none in our
+// tree post-migration, but keeps API surface stable for any third-party
+// code or tests that might bind to musicCallback directly).
 void myMusicPlayer(void *udata, uint8_t *stream, int len)
 {
   musicCallback(udata, stream, len);
@@ -375,7 +442,46 @@ bool Organya::start(int startBeat)
       = std::bind(&Organya::_musicCallback, this, std::placeholders::_1, std::placeholders::_2, std::placeholders::_3);
   _setPlayPosition(startBeat);
   song.Synth();
-  Mix_HookMusic(myMusicPlayer, NULL);
+
+  // DOS-PORT: SDL2_mixer's Mix_HookMusic(callback, NULL) is replaced by
+  // the SDL3 AudioStream → MIX_Track binding pattern. See the
+  // organyaStreamCallback comment block at the top of this file for the
+  // architectural rationale; here we just wire it up.
+  //
+  // Lazy-create the stream + track on first start. Both kept alive
+  // across pause/resume/stop; explicitly destroyed in shutdown().
+  if (!_organya_stream)
+  {
+    SDL_AudioSpec spec = { SDL_AUDIO_S16, 2, SAMPLE_RATE };
+    _organya_stream = SDL_CreateAudioStream(&spec, &spec);
+    if (!_organya_stream)
+    {
+      LOG_ERROR("SDL_CreateAudioStream (Organya): {}", SDL_GetError());
+      return false;
+    }
+    if (!SDL_SetAudioStreamGetCallback(_organya_stream, organyaStreamCallback, this))
+    {
+      LOG_ERROR("SDL_SetAudioStreamGetCallback (Organya): {}", SDL_GetError());
+    }
+  }
+  if (!_organya_track)
+  {
+    MIX_Mixer *mixer = SoundManager::getInstance()->mixer();
+    _organya_track   = MIX_CreateTrack(mixer);
+    if (!_organya_track)
+    {
+      LOG_ERROR("MIX_CreateTrack (Organya): {}", SDL_GetError());
+      return false;
+    }
+    if (!MIX_SetTrackAudioStream(_organya_track, _organya_stream))
+    {
+      LOG_ERROR("MIX_SetTrackAudioStream (Organya): {}", SDL_GetError());
+    }
+  }
+  if (!MIX_PlayTrack(_organya_track, 0))
+  {
+    LOG_ERROR("MIX_PlayTrack (Organya): {}", SDL_GetError());
+  }
   return true;
 }
 
@@ -397,7 +503,12 @@ uint32_t Organya::stop()
     }
 
     song.playing = false;
-    Mix_HookMusic(NULL, NULL);
+    // DOS-PORT: SDL2_mixer's Mix_HookMusic(NULL, NULL) deactivated the
+    // global music callback. SDL3 equivalent: stop the track. Track and
+    // stream stay alive across stops; reused on next start(). Final
+    // teardown happens in shutdown() at process exit.
+    if (_organya_track)
+      MIX_StopTrack(_organya_track, 0);
     return cur_beat;
   }
   return 0;
diff --git a/src/sound/Organya.h b/src/sound/Organya.h
index 37afe43..4d270b5 100644
--- a/src/sound/Organya.h
+++ b/src/sound/Organya.h
@@ -9,6 +9,8 @@
 #include "../Singleton.h"
 #include "SoundManager.h"
 
+#include <SDL3/SDL.h>
+#include <SDL3_mixer/SDL_mixer.h>
 #include <cstdint>
 #include <map>
 #include <memory>
@@ -77,6 +79,13 @@ public:
   void resume();
   void _musicCallback(void *udata, uint8_t *stream, uint32_t len);
 
+  // DOS-PORT: SDL3 audio-stream "produce on demand" callback. Defined
+  // as a free function in Organya.cpp; needs access to _s16_scratch
+  // (private) and _musicCallback (public). friend declaration grants
+  // _s16_scratch access without exposing it as a public API.
+  friend void SDLCALL organyaStreamCallback(void *userdata, SDL_AudioStream *stream,
+                                            int additional_amount, int total_amount);
+
 protected:
   friend class Singleton<Organya>;
 
@@ -104,6 +113,27 @@ private:
   float volume            = 1.0;
   bool fading             = false;
   uint32_t last_fade_time = 0;
+
+  // DOS-PORT: SDL3 audio pipeline replaces SDL2_mixer's Mix_HookMusic
+  // global "music callback" hook. The new model is:
+  //   _musicCallback (unchanged S16-internal synth) writes into _s16_scratch
+  //          ↓
+  //   _organya_stream (SDL_AudioStream) receives S16 stereo via
+  //          SDL_PutAudioStreamData inside an SDL_AudioStreamCallback
+  //          ↓
+  //   _organya_track (MIX_Track) is bound to the stream via
+  //          MIX_SetTrackAudioStream; the mixer pulls from the stream as
+  //          it needs frames; SDL3 audio device handles S16→device-format
+  //          conversion downstream of us.
+  //
+  // Lazy-created on first start(); kept alive across pause/resume/stop so
+  // we don't re-allocate per song. Explicitly destroyed in shutdown().
+  // Synchronous-only: the stream callback runs on SDL3-DOS's cooperative
+  // audio pump — no SDL_CreateThread anywhere in this path (per
+  // docs/SDL3-MIGRATION.md § 3 invariant).
+  MIX_Track       *_organya_track  = nullptr;
+  SDL_AudioStream *_organya_stream = nullptr;
+  std::vector<int16_t> _s16_scratch;  // resize-on-demand, never shrinks
 };
 
 } // namespace Sound
